# Keep truecopy's own tree LF everywhere. Skill content is hashed byte-exact
# (CRLF != LF — see loadSkillDir), so a committed truecopy.lock's hashes stay
# stable across contributor OSes only if the bytes don't get rewritten by git's
# autocrlf. `text=auto` still auto-detects binary fixtures and leaves them alone.
* text=auto eol=lf
